    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00baC/ 220\u00baC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Put a large <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>dried yeast </strong>to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>warm water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add your<strong> tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pizza base mix</strong> to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[115ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>warm</strong> <strong>water</strong> (you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the dough out onto a <strong>floured</strong> work surface and cut into 1 per person</p><p>Toss each <strong>dough</strong> <strong>ball</strong> in a light dusting of <strong>flour</strong> until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Press each <strong>dough</strong> <strong>ball</strong> in the centre and gently push outwards with your fingertips, leaving the rim of the pizza untouched to form a crust (don't worry if the dough rips, just stick it back together and carry on!)</p><p>Tip: Dust with an extra sprinkling of flour as you go to stop it sticking!</p><p>Keep going until your base is approx. 18-20cm in diameter, then roughly mould into a heart shape (it doesn't need to be perfect!) \u2013 these are your <strong>heart-shaped pizza base[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the baking tray[s] from the oven (careful the tray[s] will be hot!)</p><p>Transfer the <strong>heart-shaped pizza base[s]</strong> to the baking tray[s], then divide the <strong>balsamic tomato sauce </strong>evenly between each pizza and spread it evenly with the back of a spoon</p><p>Tip: To pick up the pizza dough, gently flip it over the back of your hand to stop it ripping!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the<strong> heart-shaped pizza base[s] </strong>with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and <strong>torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>stilton cheese</strong> on the top and spoon over your <strong>soft cheese</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2 or more? Make sure the pizzas don't overlap on the tray to avoid raw dough!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-18 min or until the cheese has melted and the crust has puffed up and browned \u2013 these are your <strong>four cheese heart-shaped pizza[s]</strong></p><p>While the pizza is cooking, wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-one-with-all-the-cheese-pizza-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>four cheese heart-shaped pizza </strong>with your <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>red chilli relish</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining balsamic vinegar </strong>over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
